ENTRY       EC 4.3.1.28                 Enzyme
NAME        L-lysine cyclodeaminase;
            rapL (gene name);
            fkbL (gene name);
            tubZ (gene name);
            visC (gene name)
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-nitrogen lyases;
            Ammonia-lyases
SYSNAME     L-lysine ammonia-lyase (cyclizing; ammonia-forming)
REACTION    L-lysine = L-pipecolate + NH3 [RN:R10277]
ALL_REAC    R10277
SUBSTRATE   L-lysine [CPD:C00047]
PRODUCT     L-pipecolate [CPD:C00408];
            NH3 [CPD:C00014]
COMMENT     Requires bound NAD+. The enzyme produces the non-proteinogenic amino acid L-pipecolate, which is incorporated into multiple secondary metabolite products, including rapamycin, tobulysin, virginiamycin and pristinamycin.
